    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into discs, approx. 1cm thick</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> potato discs</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, then season generously with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-30 min or until the potatoes are cooked through and crispy \u2013 these are your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are in the oven, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and<strong> soft cheese </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> creamy stock</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and add to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pour the <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>stock</strong> all over the spinach</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> on top of the spinach and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>grated cheese</strong> all over the<strong> cod</strong></p><p>Drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 16-20 min or until the cod is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy cod & spinach gratin</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-cod-and-spinach-gratin-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy cod & spinach gratin</strong> with the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
